# CLI & MCP

- CLI uses **ArgumentParser** (`Sources/mf/MF.swift`). Subcommands should support scripting; prefer `--json` where metrics are machine-readable.
- MCP lives in `MCPServer.swift`: **stdio JSON-RPC**, tools like `get_status`, `get_battery`, `set_fan_mode`, `check_version`, `run_update`. Keep tool names stable; document new tools in `README.md` and `examples/mcp.json`.
- MCP must remain **local-only** (no network relay). Heavy work should call `MasterFabricCore` services.
- `mf menubar` launches the installed app path under `~/.local`; if missing, tell the user to run `make install`.
- `mf update` / version check talk to the public GitHub repo — fail gracefully offline; never embed tokens for GitHub API.

```text
✅ Add tool + README row + examples/mcp.json note
❌ Rename existing MCP tool without migration note
```
